Real-hardware screenshots from wave 7 (Cirrus + UNIVBE,
/tmp/cirrus7/IMG_2777.jpeg and IMG_2780.jpeg) show green-text overlay
lines composited over the rendered framebuffer with content like:

  [09:52:00] [info] flip-probe: renderer=software window_ptr=...
  [09:52:00] [info] Sound system init
  BLASTER: Opening at 22050 Hz, 2 channels, format 0x8010, ...
  LOADING..
  gameloop: iter 2 ticks=43287 mapno=-1

These match DEBUG.LOG content exactly. The path is the
Logger_djgpp.h shim's per-line `fwrite(_buf.data(), 1, _buf.size(),
stderr);` (also any stray printf / SDL_Log / abort messages). On DOS
in graphics mode the BIOS / VGA hardware still composites text-mode
console writes (INT 21h / INT 10h) onto the same display alongside the
SDL3-DOS framebuffer, producing the overlay.

Fix: redirect stdout and stderr to NUL via freopen() at the top of
main(), before Logger::init / SDL_Init. DEBUG.LOG remains intact —
Logger.cpp opens its own FILE* via std::fopen(filename, "w") which is
independent of the freopen'd standard streams. Smoke-tested under
DOSBox-X parity; DEBUG.LOG continues to flush per-line (patch 0036
fsync) and reaches the title scene normally.

Cost: lose the stderr-mirror of LOG_* lines, but the file sink is
canonical and stderr-mirror was always invisible in graphics mode
anyway. Lose any unstructured printf/abort warnings, which are
acceptable to silence in a graphics-mode game.

Patch lives only on DOS targets (`__DJGPP__ || NXE_DOS`) — Linux/Mac/
Windows builds keep the standard streams.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 src/main.cpp | 23 +++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 23 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/main.cpp b/src/main.cpp
index 7652352..5f091ae 100644
--- a/src/main.cpp
+++ b/src/main.cpp
@@ -2,6 +2,7 @@
 #include "nx.h"
 
 #include <cstdarg>
+#include <cstdio>
 #include <cstdlib>
 #if !defined(_WIN32)
 #include <unistd.h>
@@ -330,6 +331,28 @@ int main(int argc, char *argv[])
 
   (void)ResourceManager::getInstance();
 
+#if defined(__DJGPP__) || defined(NXE_DOS)
+  // DOS-PORT (patch 0049, Phase 9 wave 8): redirect stdout/stderr to NUL
+  // before Logger::init / SDL_Init so that any libc / SDL_Log / spdlog-
+  // shim writes to the standard streams do NOT reach the DOS console. On
+  // real hardware (Cirrus + UNIVBE confirmed wave 7, /tmp/cirrus7/IMG_2777
+  // and IMG_2780) DOS routes stdout/stderr writes through INT 21h to the
+  // VGA text-mode console. While SDL3-DOS owns the framebuffer in graphics
+  // mode, the BIOS / VGA hardware still composites text-mode writes onto
+  // the same display, producing green-text overlay lines on top of the
+  // game. The Logger_djgpp.h shim writes every LOG_* call to stderr in
+  // addition to djgpp_log_fp; the file path is the canonical sink we want
+  // and it stays intact (Logger::init's std::fopen(filename) is unaffected
+  // by freopen(stderr,...)). Any non-logger printf paths (SDL warnings,
+  // libc abort messages, etc.) also vanish, which is the correct behavior
+  // for a graphics-mode game.
+  //
+  // DEBUG.LOG file logging is unaffected — Logger.cpp opens its own FILE*
+  // via std::fopen, independent of the freopen'd stdio streams.
+  std::freopen("NUL", "w", stdout);
+  std::freopen("NUL", "w", stderr);
+#endif
+
   Logger::init(ResourceManager::getInstance()->getPrefPath("debug.log"));
 //  SDL_LogSetAllPriority(SDL_LOG_PRIORITY_VERBOSE);
 
